title: An artists depiction of the Kepler space telescope - St. Cloud Times
text:
Has Kepler spotted an 'alien megastructure?' Strange light emitting from a distant star has astronomers and people in the scientific community scratching their heads. Check out this story on sctimes.com: http://usat.ly/1LvYpL1 Is a megastructure created by an alien civilization diverting the light to create energy? Or is it just leftover particles from an asteroid belt? Maybe, a technical glitch? Spotted by NASA's Kepler Space Telescope in 2009, the strange light pattern emitted from the star has puzzled many over the years.
Start the conversation, or Read more at St. Cloud Times.
